msIdentifier.repository: Library at the Herbert D. Katz Center for Advanced Judaic Studies

msContents.summary: Shorter commentary on Talkhīṣ al-Miftāḥ by Jalāl al-Dīn al-Qazwīnī, an abridgment of part 3 of Miftāḥ al-ʻulūm by al-Sakkākī on al-Maʻānī wa-al-bayān. This copy is missing a page at the beginning and is written in an ink that is corroding through the paper making some of the pages unstable and difficult to read.

author.persName: Qazwīnī, Jalāl al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn ʻAbd al-Raḥmān, 1267 or 1268-1338
قزويني، جلال الدين محمد بن عبد الرحمن،

respStmt.name: Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning

support.watermark: Trefoil countermark with initials B? and C?; some pages have a large coat of arms (see f. 56 for example).

supportDesc.extent: i, 175 leaves : 279 x 197 (205 x 120) mm bound to 275 x 205 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Source-text overlined in black; some chapter headings in larger script.

decoNote.n: Inside back cover flap open to show design

binding.p: Red leather over pasteboard with flap (Type II); blind-stamped central mandorla, two pendants on the vertical axis and double frame; binding is detached from textblock.

origin.p: The copy is undated, though it mentions that the work copied was begun in 742 and finished in 748 A.H. (f. 175r); possibly copied in the 17th or 18th century.

history.provenance: Given by Solomon L. Skoss to the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning (note on library bookplate, inside front cover).
Formerly owned by the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning (note on library bookplate, inside front cover).
